DATA CLOUD
Data Cloud Standard Permission Sets

A permission set defines the level of access and visibility that Salesforce users have to data and features in Data Cloud. Six standard permission sets are provided for Data Cloud. The Salesforce admin assigns permission sets to users. We don’t recommend creating a custom permission set for Data Cloud access, however you can combine the permissions sets with other Salesforce permission sets.

TIP To determine your org's Data Cloud license, in Setup, go to Permission Sets, and review the license field for your Data Cloud standard permission sets. If the license is Data Cloud, this article describes your org's standard permission sets. If the license is Customer Data Platform, see Customer Data Platform Standard Permission Sets in Data Cloud instead.
IMPORTANT Data Cloud orgs began receiving new permission sets starting in December 2023. All Data Cloud orgs except orgs with Marketing Cloud Growth enabled received new permissions sets by April 20, 2024. See Data Cloud Permission Set Names During the Enhanced Security Migration Period to understand naming differences in the legacy standard permission sets and new standard permission sets.
Data Cloud Standard Permission Sets

You can combine these Data Cloud permission sets with other Salesforce permission sets for users who need additional access.

Data Cloud Admin—Users with this permission set can access all functionality within Data Cloud, including mapping data to the data model and creating data streams, identity resolution rulesets, and calculated insights.

To manage and assign users in Setup and access Data Cloud Setup, you must be a Data Cloud Admin and have a Salesforce administrator role that grants access to Salesforce Setup. If you have access to Salesforce Setup, you can set up the application, and access Salesforce Sales and Service clouds and other integrated Salesforce systems.

Data Cloud User—Users with this permission set can view Data Cloud features.

Segmentation and Activation Add-On License Standard Permission Sets

Data Cloud orgs with the segmentation and activation add-on license have the standard Data Cloud permission sets, plus marketing-specific permission sets. You can combine Data Cloud permission sets with other Salesforce permission sets for users who need additional access. For more information about this add-on license, contact your account executive.

Data Cloud Marketing Admin—Users with this permission set can manage day-to-day configuration needs, support, maintenance, and improvement and perform regular internal system audits.

To manage and assign users in Setup and access Data Cloud Setup, you must be a Data Cloud Marketing Admin and have a Salesforce administrator role that grants access to Salesforce Setup. If you have access to Salesforce Setup, you can set up the application, and access Salesforce Sales and Service clouds and other integrated Salesforce systems.

Data Cloud Data Aware Specialist—Users with this permission set can map data to the data model and create data streams, identity resolution rulesets, and calculated insights.

Data Cloud Marketing Manager—Users with this permission set can manage an overall segmentation strategy, including creating activation targets and activations.

Data Cloud Marketing Specialist—Users with this permission set can create segments.

TIP We recommend assigning standard permission sets to users instead of creating custom permission sets. Data Cloud standard permission sets are automatically updated with each release as new features become available. Using a custom permission set could result in users not having access to new features or functionality.
Customer Data Platform Standard Permission Sets in Data Cloud
A permission set defines the level of access and visibility that Salesforce users have to data and features in Data Cloud. Four standard permission sets are provided for Data Cloud orgs contracted under a Customer Data Platform license. The Salesforce admin assigns permission sets to users.
Data Cloud Permission Set Names During the Enhanced Security Migration Period
Starting in November 2023, the existing Data Cloud standard permission sets were renamed and new permission sets with similar names were created in every Data Cloud org. Refer to these tables to understand the new names for existing permission sets and names of equivalent new permission sets.
Custom Permission Sets in Data Cloud
To create a Data Cloud custom permission set, we recommend cloning an existing standard Data Cloud permission set. Some Data Cloud features can’t be accessed with permission sets created from scratch.
